Package com.server.interfaces

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Listener
    Listeners are responsible for listening for input from a Sender over a Socket connection.
    Sender
    Senders are responsible for transmitting ComparableCommands to the connected Listener over a Socket connection.
    Server
    Servers are responsible for accepting Socket connections, and spinning off Listeners and Senders to communicate with Clients.
    Trace
    Traces are used for logging purposes.
